# Technical Implementation Specification: Diagnostics, Logging, Security, & Bay Mapping

This document provides a comprehensive technical blueprint to implement a **Hybrid Logging Subsystem**, a **Localhost-Bypassed Network Security Gate**, a **Support Bundle Compiler**, and an **Interactive Admin/Diagnostics Panel (Tab 3)** on the Drive Sanitization Station (running on Ubuntu 26.04).

---

## 1. Directory Structure Additions & Requirements

To prevent configuration drift, ensure the local storage layout on the host is explicitly updated. The application data directory (`/opt/drive-eraser/data`) must be structured as follows:

```text
/opt/drive-eraser/
├── data/
│   ├── wipes.db                  # SQLite database
│   ├── certs/                    # JSON/HTML certificates
│   └── logs/                     # [NEW] Root logs directory
│       ├── app.log               # [NEW] Global INFO-level application output
│       ├── active/               # [NEW] Ephemeral logs for running jobs (e.g., job-124.log)
│       └── failed/               # [NEW] Post-mortem logs for failed jobs (e.g., failed-job-124-bay3.log)
└── config/
    ├── policy.json               # Updated to include "lan_passphrase"
    └── bay_map.json              # Write-enabled from UI
```

